parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
a loud whining or moaning noise is heard from the fuel pump
the fuel pump fails to distribute fuel to the engine
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the transmission to slip, hesitate, or fail to engage, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The "PRND" lights on the dashboard may flash
the transmission may slip or hesitate
the vehicle may not shift into gear
or the vehicle may not move at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition coil failure can cause the engine to shake violently, lose power, and stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
Electrical system malfunctions can cause various electrical functions to shut off, including power windows, locks, and lights, leading to safety hazards and inconvenience.
symptoms: power windows and locks not working

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, and potential accidents.
Headlight failure can reduce visibility, leading to accidents and safety hazards.
Battery and electrical component failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to safety hazards and inconvenience.
Transmission control module failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to safety hazards and inconvenience.
